Vulkan Phase 3: full kernel parity with ROCm

PARENT: tsk-44.
STATUS: planned, not started. Depends on Phase 2.

GOAL
Port every remaining wrapper/kernel exposed by ds4_rocm.c so that swapping the Vulkan backend in for ROCm produces correct end-to-end output on the production model.

KERNEL INVENTORY (from ds4_rocm.c, current head)
- Matmul family: Q8_0 (decode + LDS variants for prefill, multiple N), Q4_K, IQ2_XXS, Q2_K, F16 (with LDS-x sharing across waves per feedback_f16_decode_lds_x), matmul_f16_pair.
- Norms: rms_norm, head_rms_norm, dsv4 norms.
- RoPE.
- Attention: full prefill, decode (incl. SWA-ring wraparound), attention_output_low_q8.
- KV cache: kv_fp8_store_raw, store_raw_kv, FP8 pack/unpack.
- MoE: router_select, routed-MoE matvec, shared MoE.
- Top-K: scalar + parallel block-K (DS4_N_INDEXER_TOP_K=512 threshold path; mirror trace env DS4_VULKAN_TOPK_TRACE).
- HC family: split sinkhorn, weighted sum, weighted_sum_norm (note metal/dsv4_hc.metal sinkhorn ordering: init + col + (row,col)*(N-1) — the bug captured in /home/noah/.claude/plans/moonlit-sprouting-graham.md, MUST match Metal exactly, not the ROCm pre-fix variant).
- get_rows / set_rows.

WORK PATTERN
For each wrapper:
1. Add the GLSL shader under shaders/.
2. Add the C wrapper in ds4_vulkan.c with descriptor set + push constants.
3. Add a STEP block in tests/ds4_vulkan_kernel_test.c using the matching ROCm CPU oracle.
4. Run ./ds4_vulkan_kernel_test — must end with OK before moving on.
5. Tick off the wrapper. Commit at clean checkpoints (per CLAUDE.md commit cadence).

DIAGNOSTICS
- Mirror DS4_ROCM_TRACE -> DS4_VULKAN_TRACE (per-call enter trace).
- Mirror DS4_ROCM_TIME=1 -> DS4_VULKAN_TIME=1 (per-wrapper histogram). On Vulkan use VkQueryPool timestamps for real GPU time, not just CPU enqueue time — addresses the gap noted in feedback_real_gpu_time.
- Mirror DS4_ROCM_SYNC_EACH=1 -> DS4_VULKAN_SYNC_EACH=1 for per-call serialization.

VALIDATION
./ds4_vulkan_kernel_test ends with OK with the full STEP set (target ~40+ tests, matching the ROCm harness count).